Event.0: Leicester City win the English Premier League title after starting the season at 5,000-1 odds
Event.1: Princess Charlotte Elizabeth Diana of Cambridge, the second child of Prince William, duke of Cambridge, and Catherine, duchess of Cambridge, was born in London.
Event.2: Osama bin Laden, the suspected mastermind behind the September 11 attacks and the FBI's most wanted man is killed by US special forces in Abbottabad, Pakistan
Event.3: Osama bin Laden—founder of the militant Islamist organization al-Qaeda and mastermind of numerous terrorist attacks, notably the September 11, 2001, attacks—was killed by U.S. forces in Abbottabad, Pakistan.
Event.4: Cyclone Nargis makes landfall in Myanmar killing over 130,000 people and leaving millions of people homeless
Event.5: First film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe released "Iron Man" directed by Jon Favreau, starring Robert Downey Jr. as Tony Stark
Event.6: British Labour Party leader Tony Blair became prime minister of the United Kingdom; he was the youngest person to hold the office since 1812.
Event.7: Falklands War: Argentine cruiser General Belgrano sunk by British submarine Conqueror, killing more than 350 men
Event.8:
David Beckham
British athlete
was born
Event.9:
Dwayne Johnson
American professional wrestler and actor
was born
Event.10: Arthur Miller wins Pulitzer Prize for "Death of a Salesman"
Event.11: An attempted prison escape by six inmates at Alcatraz resulted in two days of violent fighting, which became known as the Battle of Alcatraz.
Event.12: World War II: Battle of Berlin ends as Soviet army takes Berlin and General Weidling surrenders
Event.13: More than 1,000,000 German soldiers officially surrender to the Western Allies in Italy and Austria
Event.14:
Lou Gehrig's 2,130-game streak ended
On this day in 1939, New York Yankee great Lou Gehrig, the “Iron Horse” of American baseball, ended his streak of consecutive games played (2,130), setting a record that stood until 1995, when it was broken by Cal Ripken, Jr.
Event.15: Sergei Prokofiev's musical "Peter and the Wolf" premieres in Moscow
Event.16: The peasants of Luzon, Philippines, rose up in arms against oppressive land tenancy laws.
Event.17: Bengali director Satyajit Ray, who brought Indian cinema to world recognition with the Apu Trilogy, was born in Calcutta (Kolkata).
Event.18:
Satyajit Ray
Indian film director
was born
Event.19: US Secretary of State James F. Byrnes marries Maude Busch
Event.20: American pediatrician Benjamin Spock—who wrote a number of influential works on child rearing, notably Common Sense Book of Baby and Child Care (1946), which sold more than 50 million copies worldwide—was born.
Event.21: Manfred, Freiherr (baron) von Richthofen (the “Red Baron”), Germany's top aviator and leading ace in World War I, was born in Breslau, Germany (now Wrocław, Poland).
Event.22:
Manfred, baron von Richthofen
German aviator
was born
Event.23: Menilek II of Ethiopia signed the Treaty of Wichale with Italy, granting it territory in northern Ethiopia in exchange for money and weaponry.
Event.24:
Theodor Herzl
Austrian Zionist leader
was born
Event.25: Léopold (Léopold I)of Saxe-Coburg, 1st King of Belgium following independence from the Netherlands marries British Princess Charlotte Augusta
Event.26: The United States purchased the Louisiana Territory from France at a rate of less than three cents per acre for 828,000 square miles (2,144,520 square km), which soon proved to be a tremendous bargain.
Event.27: Daughter of the Prince of Orange, Albertine Agnes marries William Frederick Prince of Nassau-Dietz
Event.28: The King James Version of the Bible was first published.
Event.29: Renaissance artist Leonardo da Vinci—whose works, notably the painting Mona Lisa, were among the most famous in the world—died in Cloux, France.
